                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="axiom_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a rule or principle that most people believe to be true</span></span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">the old axiom that you can only succeed through hard work</span></li></ul><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="axiom_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">late 15th cent.: from French <span class="ei">axiome</span> or Latin <span class="ei">axioma</span>, from Greek <span class="ei">axiōma</span> ‘what is thought fitting’, from <span class="ei">axios</span> ‘worthy’.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
